  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6758.24 sitting just above the GEX flip at 6725 but trapped within massive negative gamma walls from 6745-6765, dealers are in amplifying mode and likely aggressively buying this move higher as they're short gamma in this zone. The regime shows PIN (positive institutional gamma) but the localized negative gamma concentration around current levels means any directional move will be accelerated by dealer hedging flows rather than dampened. Watch 6755 (-7567M) as the key resistance level where dealer buying pressure peaks, while a break below 6745 would trigger even more aggressive dealer buying into weakness.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile whipsaw action between 6745-6765 with dealers amplifying both moves up and down.",
